Game Notes
~~~~~~~~~~
Seven: The Days Long Gone is an open-world, isometric role-playing game, in
which you play as Teriel, a master thief sent on a mission that will shake
the foundations of the Vetrall Empire. Free roam across the vibrant prison
island of Peh, and choose whether to help or exploit its many citizens.
If there's one place that Master Thief Teriel avoids at all costs, it's the
prison island of Peh. But when a daring heist takes an unexpected turn,
Teriel finds himself shackled on an airship bound for the infamous island.
To make matters worse, the daemon inside his head makes it very clear that
the thief will never leave unless he does exactly what he's told.
In Seven: The Days Long Gone you play as Teriel. You must use all of your
cunning and clandestine skills to escape a web of deceit and betrayal, and
ultimately survive Peh.
